messages.content: "Proposal the first! You stabbed the emperor." She stabs Aeolian for 3 damage playfully.

Theo misses his attack.

It's Aeolian's turn.
“Not true. You can confirm yourself; I was with you the moment we both heard a commotion.” I defend.
((What is your action))

((I will unarmed strike her. This does 1+STR damage on a hit, which is 0.))

((6 to hit))

It misses. 

She decides to play along because Aeolian would pass out immediately otherwise. She punches him for 1 damage. "That was simply the time he was discovered. If he was seen being stabbed, there would be no mystery. Your alibi fails."

"Do you... Actually think he did it?" Theo is ignored.
“The emperor was stabbed by a sword. I verifiably brought no weapons into the event, and have no means to access such a thing.” I dagger.
((12 to hit))
It hits. "I concede the obvious. You’re innocent. Your turn to argue."
((3 damage if that matters))
“It seems somewhat likely the hellhounds were involved, particularly Linjamin’s ilk.” The dagger again.
It misses. "You think the faceless carried out the assassination attempt? Why would they have been in the castle?" She hits Aeolian for 1 damage.
“For a job. They’re contract killers.” Same thing.
((FIVE.))

It misses.

"I meant… How would they have gotten in? Security should’ve been tighter for the party! There’s no way any member of the hellhounds could enter the party."
She misses as well.
“And what if someone in a position of power created a gap for them to slip through?” Again.
((Five.))

A miss.

She smiles, seeming genuinely interested. "Who are you accusing?"

I hesitate.

“…Asturian, perhaps.”
"Asturian hadn’t been in the country in decades until last night. He wouldn’t have had the formal power to accomplish this." She punches Aeolian for 2 damage.
“Ghrk. He wasn’t involved in the event’s setup, then…? The Duchess is also suspicious by association…”
"Could I not say the same of you?"
“Hah. Perhaps. We could make an argument of motive, but… that’s not concrete…”

"I’ll argue the premise then. The faceless did not kill the emperor." She provides Aeolian with bardic inspiration for some deep metaphorical reason. "Because the face of the intruder who attacked the emperor was seen."

"What!?" Theo.

Aliza decided this provides enough of a cool reaction to not be ignored. "The assailant also attacked Asturian and, as I indicated, he did not have any kind of mask. Attacking the emperor without their mask and without a sword is unthinkable for a member of the faceless!”
“He attacked Asturian…?”

"Yes. Asturian told my father earlier. It seems like Asturian was rather humiliated by the outcome of the fight against a magic user." Aliza smirks and puts away her weapon, ending initiative. ((200xp)) "My father also informed me Donald Jameson, a hellhound leader, somehow snuck into the party. I believe this is his work rather than Linjamin’s."
“I see.” I see.
She holds her hand out. "I was actually hoping to work with you on this. It seems interesting and you have more power to look where I can’t."
I take it. “That seems wise.”

She shakes it. "I hope you find my skills entitle me to plow through the riches of your emersonian mind some more."

Theo avoids mentioning he has no idea what she just said.
“Yyesss.” I nod.
"It’s late tonight, but shall we meet in the morning?" Aliza.
“Sure.”
She leaves.
I enter my home.
Theo follows because he’s a weirdo like that.
“I am going to get some clerical work done and then sleep. Thank you, Mulligan.”
"No problem, sir! We can always try harder tomorrow." Theo leaves.
I adjourn to my quarters.
The house is normal this time.
Yyess. I get some architectural planning work done before heading to bed.

…

Aeolian is standing in the middle of the terrain fixture commonly referred to as a marsh. A shadow of a dragon looms over him, but attempting to look at its source causes Aeolian to become blinded by sunlight. "Welcome, descendant of the Burr line."
“Mmmyes. What.”
"You have been caught in a clash that shall perhaps determine the future of the Soltarian empire. Are you prepared?"
"As much as one can be."
"I am a guide to the future of this empire. Do you accept the burden of being guided?"
"So long as I can determine how I accept or ignore this guidance myself."
"Answer my questions and I shall give you direction towards the truth. Tell me… Did Imperial Prince Asturian VII stab the emperor?"
“…Probably not personally, no.”
"Correct. Why was he absent then when the body was discovered?"
"A good question. Perhaps because he was trying to ensure an alibi?"

"Incorrect. Imperial Prince Asturian VII would have come to the scene if he could."

Aeolian wakes up. ((End session))
It's Nash's turn.
Nash attempts to hit the magical construct with his longsword.
((Roll))
((unarmed strike has +4 to hit. does that same modifier apply to an armed strike))
((Is your rapier not equipped?))
((oh no lmao i'm a dumbass. hold on i'm going to use my longsword instead))
((19 to hit w/ longsword))
It hits.
((4 damage))

The armor strikes back for 5 damage on Nash and a second attack that hits.

Ruth punches it a total of 4 times because Monks are kind of busted, only hitting once for 7 damage.

Orion enters the battle and launches an arrow at the armor, just barely missing.

It's Nash's turn again.
"Shit-" Nash hisses, clinging pained to his side. His breath comes out strangled and slow. *If it ain't broke, don't fix it, right?*
He hits it with his longsword again.
((6 to hit))
It misses.
"Fuck."

The armour swings at Ruth twice, missing one. It deals 5 damage.

Ruth punches it twice and only hits once for 7 damage.

Orion hits it with an arrow for another 7 damage. "What the hell is this thing!?"

"It’s protecting someone called the Sunslayer!" Ruth. 

It’s Nash’s turn.
Nash casts Searing Smite.

The armour strikes Orion for 6 damage.

Ruth misses her punches twice.

Orion misses a shot as well. "Sunslayer? Like… The empire of the sun, the Soltarian empire?" 

It’s Nash's turn.
((sorry i didn't make things clear enough initially before being distracted, i need to do a con roll for searing smite to succeed))
((it needs to be at least 12 and i rolled 11, meaning it failed))
((now onto my proper turn that should've happened last round))
Nash attempts to hit it with the longsword, again.
((mean to me))
((That’s not what searing smite does))
((i'm reading the dnd page..........))
((The constitution roll is for people who are hit by the weapon))
((weh))
((how DOES searing smite actually work then..))
((Yes. I didn’t realize it was a bonus action though so you do get to attack still yeah))
Nash attempts to hit it with the longsword for real this time.
It misses.
Now it’s his turn chronologically again.
Nash hits it with the longsword. This time for sure.
It misses.

The armour hits Ruth for 6 damage.

Ruth successfully smashes the armour to pieces with 2 punches. ((200xp, end initiative))

"Good job, captain." Orion takes a shaky breath.
((is there a way you can easily change from milestone advancement to exp advancement on dndbeyond lmao i set it up wrong))
((Idk))
((Ask publicly ig))
((ok wait i figured it out))
Nash exhales, wiping sweat from his brow. *Ruth got the kill, huh..? Haha.. good for her. Yeah.* He thinks to himself.

Ruth looks through the hole in the other wall. "This seems like the catacombs under the city. An outsider must have slipped here to commit the murder and established this trap to anyone following them."

"The Sunslayer, you mean? It must be that they were trying to destroy the empire with the emperor’s death." Orion.
Nash nods in agreement with Orion.

The armour begins to move again, causing the party to assume a combat stance once again. It turns to stare at Ruth. "You have passed the test."

"No shit, you useless metal punching bag." Ruth.

"I have nothing more to do. The Sunslayer awaits." The armour begins folding into itself, causing a horrible screeching of metal.
"What???" Nash says, confused.
It folds into a singular sheet of metal with bizarre engravings on it.
Nash tries to get closer to the sheet of metal, and examine it.
It is as described. ((Roll history ig))

It appears to be written in Old Soltarian but you aren’t familiar enough to understand what it means.

Ruth suddenly notices 2 people trying to sneak through. "Who are you?"

One of them is Selle(who looks different from at the party) and the other is this foreign man.
"And how exactly would I prove that?"

"We can do it while we make our way somewhere. Hold on to this."
Selle writes down a note with the contents wrapped up tightly so it isn't immediately visible. The note contains a scribbled drawing of a cat.
They hand it to Erik.
"It's a decently lengthy journey to a place where we can stay the night, hold on to this note,  and do not open it until we get near there, I'll say when that is. After we're there, I'll ask you to give it back." 
The note is folded in a way where you can tell if it's been opened after the fact that it's been folded over.
"I see. Interesting test." He pockets it.

"Let's proceed." 
Selle leads the way to an area in the catacombs roughly 3/4s of the way to Laura's base.
((Roll stealth to avoid monsters))
( nat 20)
They expertly avoid all of the creatures lurking in the catacombs. They can hear a commotion in the distance.
"Do you hear that?" Selle whispers to Erik.
"Yes. I think that might be *that* thing."

*Why is it near HERE? I feel like we have to go closer to it though...*
"Damn it. Any ideas?"
"It went into the catacombs, didn’t it? That’s what the major told us."
"Yeah. But this area is..."
((Roll perception for where it sounds like it’s coming from))
Selle has no idea what entrance to the catacombs is closest to this commotion.

Selle swears under her breath.
"What do we do?"
"We’re very well hidden. It might be worth scouting him out."

"Alright."
Selle and Erik come closer to attempt to scout out the commotion.

They discover a hole in the wall that leads into a strange looking room with a display case in the center. Nash Edwardson and 2 other people are currently fighting a suit of armour made of magic. They are not spotted due to their Nat 20 stealth.

*I saw this person at the party! What's going on here?*
"Is that the monster you remember seeing?" Selle whispers to Erik.

"No. These looks like guards." Erik cautiously slips through a hole in the wall opposite of the one they’re currently looking through. There is a normal door to this room but it’s closed and opening it would require a separate attempt to be stealthy.

*This is so risky.* 
Selle follows Erik.

They’re in the castle basement now. Selle can recognize this as a room they passed by while following Asturian, though the wall had not been broken open then.

"The atmosphere here is different." Erik.

*The castle basement. This is incredibly close to where Asturian tried to "prove" his birthright to the throne...*
Selle feels on edge.
"What are we gonna do? We're both incredibly weak right now."
"Is something in this area?" Erik.
"This... this is the imperial castle basement."
"What!? It connects to the catacombs?"
"Yeah. The catacombs are immensely expansive. They connect to everywhere. It makes sense now why there's an Edwardson here."
"Who?"

"It's a family that has great control over Soltaria. The Duchess owns most of the land in the city, and her daughter is the High Priestess that almost killed us at Iono's. Back there was another member of their family, although I don't know as much about him."
"I see. Someone with that much control over the city, huh?" ((Roll insight))
There’s something in his expression that gives Selle the impression he already knew this information.
There’s a horrible screeching noise of metal in the room they just left. Erik looks. "Looks like our time's up. We should head back."
"Yeah. Let's get out of here."
((Roll stealth again))

The woman looks at you 2 as you try to pass. "Who are you?"

((New channel))
Nash instinctively swivels around, pointing his longsword at the two people who've entered. "And who're *you*?"
((The woman on Nash’s side is the one who asked this for note))
((Sorry if that was unclear))

Selle feels a cold sweat down their back.
"Just some lost souls..."
((Does Selle look like the person in the picture?))

"You can call me Erik. I’m not from around here. Just got turned around." Erik, presumably.

"Yes, because foreigners usually get turned around in the castle with bloodstained clothes." The authoritative-looking woman assumes a monk combat stance.

Erik sighs. "This isn’t mine."

"That was not the part we were questioning!" Loser looking guy on team Nash.
((They look like juni's pfp yeah))
((ok but not like the image of the person who was given to me))
((No. They look like this now))
Nash doesn't lower his guard. "How did you get in here?"
"We just stumbled upon a hole in the wall here when we were coming through the catacombs, we're a bit lost as you can see." Selle tries to put on a smile.
Nash's mouth twitches reflexively, a mocking imitation of... *whatever* Selle is trying to do. "And why were you in the catacombs, my good sir?"
"Haha... well, we were just trying to find a shortcut to another part of the city. The undercity is quite the troublesome place, you know?"

"We were- Agh!" Erik suddenly falls over, clutching his own chest desperately as if trying to dig through it. "Shit… We’re not ready!"

The scrawny looking loser aims his bow at the man on the ground. "Ready for what?"
"Erik! What's wrong?"

"Shut uuuuuup!" A massive hulking man enters the room from the hole in the wall leading to the catacombs. His fists are as big as barrels and covered in dried blood. There’s a short bit of black hair on top of his head. His proportions are completely inexplicable however, he seems to undergoing a constant strain just to balance the tiny proportions of his body to their absolute gigantic size of muscle. "Leave Grognaut alone!!!!"

"Wh-What the fuck is that thing…?" The archer drops his bow and backs away nervously.

"That’s… That’s it, Yule. That’s the monster." Erik.
"What the shit?" Nash backs away also.
"Damn it! Fuck fuck fuck! Listen, you! We are way. way way too weak for this right now. We need to get out NOW." Selle speaks to Nash.
Nash (who is already wounded, for note), just grins. "*Haaaaah?* Who're you to say what I can handle? Stuuupid commoner, you - ghrk." He cuts himself off, wincing in pain.
"If you don't want your head caved in, tell us a way out of here! I don't have time for your bullshit." Selle, also visibly injured, has a worried expression and is sweating a lot.

Erik gets up from the ground and unsheathes a sword. "We’ve got our backs pressed against the wall. It’s him or the acting emperor." Erik turns to the creature. "You mentioned a Grognaut. What the hell is that?"

"I'm Grognaut! Don’t mock me!" He swings his fist down on where Erik is standing, with Erik just barely dodging this.

"Gh... ahaha...." Nash mumbles incoherently. "That's what I was waiting for, an opponent who, thefukcign,..m,." He rambles incoherently, still quite dazed, and stumbles over to the guy known only as scrawny loser/archer guy to lean on him for support.

"This guy is obsessed with alcohol! Does anyone have any?!"
Selle casts Minor Illusion behind Grognaut that plays a loud sound similar to a bottle of alcohol being dropped.
"You don’t know me! Grognaut can stop at any time! And I can hear you!!!!!" He swings his arm angrily at all of them. ((Everyone roll a dex save))

They avoid the shortsighted attack. 

"Squad! Follow me!" The monk woman dives through the hole in the wall behind Grognaut and starts running.

"Is she insane!?" The archer attempts to do the same.
"Fuuuuuuuck!!! Let's go!!!" Selle also tries to follow, gesturing for Erik to do the same.
"Urgh..! You morons... this was our opportunity to... whatever." Nash grumbles, following the archer.
((Roll dexterity!!))

Nash makes it through but Selle, Erik, and the archer are stuck in this room. 

"Shit!" The monk punches Grognaut’s leg twice. "Nash, help me make a bigger opening!"
"Fuck-!" Nash hisses. He hits the wall with his sword in an effort to do this.
((Roll strength))

A few bricks collapse onto Grognaut’s foot, widening the opening but causing him to enter barbarian rage. He swings at Nash with such force that Nash’s head doesn’t even have time to realize it’s no longer on his shoulders.

((Split channels))

Nash Edwardson has died. 

His companions fall to the ground in shock.

Erik just goes through the newly expanded opening while Grognaut is distracted.
Selle follows, but is clearly in shock.
((Roll dexterity))
They make it back through to the catacombs. Erik just books it right back to where they were before they heard the commotion.
Selle peers backwards and decides that it would be trouble to be involved, and so follows Erik.
"Shit… Where’s that place of yours from here?"
"Wait... Let me catch my breath... It should be... that way..." Selle points in a direction towards Laura's base.
Erik heads there.
Selle follows.

Laura Craig looks at you 2 with a disappointed sigh. "2 nights in a row?"

"The church, empire, and some monster are all after us. Cut your friend some slack." Erik.
"We just had... multiple near death experiences... in a row... and just saw multiple people die right... in front of our eyes... Ugh..." Selle falls onto the couch.
"I don't care about the note anymore... Feel free to open it." Selle to Erik.

"It’s fine." He tosses it to Laura. 

"Was Donald’s case really that bad?" Laura sighs. "You are not both fitting on my couch, anyway."

"It’s fine. I’ll take the floor. I’m used to it." Erik.
"It sucked. But we have all the information we need... We just need a rest and a way to contact the guy..." Selle does a big sigh.

"The leader of Destiny is being held in the church of libra, if you weren’t aware. Probably Librapilling him into being a youth pastor or something." Laura says this in an annoyed tone as she turns away from them.

Erik doesn’t respond and just lays on the ground.
"Ugh... At least he isn't dead..." Selle lays face flat on the couch.
"Yeah, night. I’ll try not to use you as a cushion while you sleep." She snickers.
Selle has no response.
((Does Selle just fall asleep then?))
((yeah

…

Selle is standing in the middle of the terrain fixture commonly referred to as a marsh. A shadow of a dragon looms over him, but attempting to look at its source causes Selle to become blinded by sunlight. "Welcome, nameless ideologue."

*...What? I thought...*
"...What's going on?"
Selle has their hand covering the light with their hand.
"You have been caught in a clash that shall perhaps determine the future of the Soltarian empire. Are you prepared?"
"...Well, if there's a chance to determine the future. I'll take it."
"I am a guide to the future of this empire. Do you accept the burden of being guided?"
"...My life almost ended twice today. I accept."
"Answer my questions and I shall give you direction towards the truth. Tell me… Did Imperial Prince Asturian VII stab the emperor?"
"No."
"Correct. Why was he absent then when the body was discovered?"
"I knocked him out. He was passed out in the basement."
"Correct. Imperial Prince Asturian VII has no prior involvement with what occurred to the emperor. Why then did he return to the empire?"
"I assume, he was told he could claim his "birthright" by coming to a place in the basement of the palace. He had a marked map."
"Correct. Why then did the map lead to nothing?"
"Perhaps they wanted him present for a deposition of Aragon."

"Incorrect. The map actually led somewhere until just a few minutes before Imperial Prince Asturian VII used it."

Selle wakes up.  ((End session))
Nash is at the gates of the court of Libra, where her freshly dead followers await her verdict. An annoyed looking attendant groans at him. "…Name?"
"Gh...?" Nash says, shocked. He looks down at himself. "I.. did it?"
"Guy Diddit? Not on the list."

He begins to laugh - first slowly, then uncontrollably. "I did it!!! I won.. ahaha... they're going to have to carry out my pieces in separate horse-drawn carts, aha, hgh.. ahaha...!!!" He doubles over. It's incomprehensible how funny it all is. "I was defending my country. I was defending my people. Now no one ever..." He trails off.
He straightens up, snapping into an uncomfortable bow. "Nash Edwardson." The pain in his lower back is grounding. "Her most honored servant. Now and forever."
"Not exactly a normal reaction." The attendant does a smug Redditor smirk.
He removes himself from the pose. "I should think it's a normal response, to dying valiantly."

"Hmm… No, it seems like your death was in the 'like a bitch’ category." That isn’t a thing. "Ah, here we go… Nash Edwardson. Hm… It’s not supposed to be your time. Libra's going to be disappointed to see you. Go in, then." He opens the gate.
He scowls. "That's not a thing." He says, but follows.

You enter my central domain, and thus I begin to communicate in the language of reality and allow your mind to translate it. Hello, Nash Edwardson. I apologize if you expected a form comprehensible to a mortal.

Nash stares up at You, his mouth dropping open in awe. "My lady... it's fine. This is exactly.. I didn't want something comprehensible to me, I knew you'd be. Like this." He's stumbling over his words.
Why are you here? It is not right for a mother to outlive her son, let alone for 2 of them to do so.
Nash blinks upwards. "I... this is what Mother wants from me. I don't understand the question."
Your mother, the duchess… She is not on my list. When she dies, she shall not come to this court. Her goals have no meaning to me, son of Edward.
"What?" He frowns. "That doesn't make sense. She's a believer. She always has been."
Are you questioning me? I understand your hesitation, but I do not produce direct lies. Merely lies of omission at most.

"No!" He tries to insist, shaking his hands frantically. "I just mean.. she's a good person, my mom. Which is why, I mean. She must be a believer. She clearly wants this from me, so. The glory of a good death.."
Your death was not glorious. Being murdered by an overgrown child is not your fate. You are needed for longer. Your family has already hired a cleric to recall your soul to the living.
"What-!" Nash chokes out. "They can't do that!!" He stomps his foot petulantly. "This was supposed to be it! Please, you have to stop them.."
Do not order things of your god. I told you, I do not lie. As such, I know everything I say to be true. My vision is correct. This is not your fate. You will do more for me.

Nash tries to calm himself, hugging himself tightly around the middle. "I.. I apologize. It was not my, intent to um, um... to demand anything of you. I will do as you say, of course. I'm forever your most loyal servant."
"Can I just.. ask one thing?"
You may.
Nash stares plaintively up at You. For a moment, he is no sort of glorious warrior, although that was really never in question. He's a spoiled little boy.
"When do I...? I mean, do you know? When I die for real? And is it.. it has to be soon, right?"
You will return soon. But first, someone else wishes to speak to you. Goodbye, Nash Edwardson.

Nash wishes he had asked something else, of course. There's a lengthy series of questions that would be befitting his lady, any amount of queries about why the world is the way it is, who's to blame for it. What Nash can do. What anyone wants from him.

But the only thing he can think to ask is when he'll be back with her. ...How selfish is that? Wanting her affection so desperately. He can't hold a god in his hands, he reminds himself in that last moment before he returns to.. wherever. He can't, so he'll just.. he'll just..
The thought becomes nothing.

…

Nash is standing in the middle of the terrain fixture commonly referred to as a marsh. A shadow of a dragon looms over him, but attempting to look at its source causes Nash to become blinded by sunlight. "Welcome, ward of the duchess."
"Argh!" Nash covers his eyes. "Who're you?!?"
"I am a guide to the future of this empire. Do you accept the burden of being guided?"
"Wah.. you're not my God." He says sulkily, still covering his eyes.
"You have been caught in a clash that shall perhaps determine the future of the Soltarian empire. Are you prepared?"
"Er... yes!" He straightens up. "I'm forever and always a servant of the empire."
"Answer my questions and I shall give you direction towards the truth. Tell me… Did Imperial Prince Asturian VII stab the emperor?"
Nash blinks in confusion. "Uh.. probably? Wait, no." He shakes his head. "It was either Asturian or the fuckin', guy in the photo. Yeah."
"It is a yes or no question."
"Er. Yes. Yeah. Yep."

"Incorrect."

Nash wakes up. ((End session))
